<p>I have a table with an arbitrary amount of columns and rows and the <strong>&lt;td&gt;</strong> tags have a height and width.  My issue is when I put it in a <strong>&lt;div&gt;</strong> with <strong>overflow:scroll</strong> and a width less than the width of the table, the table cells get squished, even though I have a specified width on them.</p>  <p>I've done a bunch of testing and it appears if I specify the width of the table, it looks fine.  There's got to be a CSS way of doing it without specifying the table width.</p>  <p>This is the gist of my code and css along with a JSFiddle demo (the number of columns doesn't matter, so long as it's greater than the width of the div</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="wrapper"&gt;     &lt;table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="Colors"&gt;         &lt;tbody&gt;             &lt;tr&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;             &lt;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;         &lt;/tbody&gt;     &lt;/table&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>CSS:</p>  <pre><code>table.Colors td {     width:25px;     height:25px;     font-size:.8em;     line-height:25px;     border:1px solid #c0c0c0;     padding:0;     margin:0; }  .wrapper {     overflow:scroll;     width:300px;     height:300px; } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/nightcatbooks/L7gwwyL4/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/nightcatbooks/L7gwwyL4/</a></p>